Subject: Administrator Phone Number preventing system settings from being saved
Description:
After updating to EPP 5.9.4.0, changes to system settings could not be saved.  I get a error message stating the Phone number from "Main Administrator Contact Details" is not valid (images attached).

Before making changes in System Configuration >> System Settings, the format of the Phone number from "Main Administrator Contact Details" was (650) 723-3333.  I had to change the phone number to 6507233333 in order to save changes.
What_We_Know__c: The issue presented by the customer was fixed in 5.9.4.1.
Next_Steps__c:
The EPP Server was updated to 5941 and the issue was addressed.
Another remote session will be set in order to apply the backend security updates.
The customer insisted on using their zoom meeting.
